@gracehuang158 @uoftmie 2T6+PEY was in the house for a #CoffeewithChris today. First off - huge shoutout to being a #Frosh group leedur @froshweek this year. Such a huge success but then - as well - all the work behind the scenes for what looking like an awesome set of @yncnuoft events coming up this year. Always a great networking opportunity. Loved the story of how she found her internships in 1st and 2nd year back in #Boston - the power of making connections on full display. I also really like hearing about her strategy for picking a university - really good perspective for sure. Fingers crossed for her foray into @survivorcbs - and working the whole strategy angle.

Are you curious about how companies navigate complex challenges and drive innovation? Join us for an exclusive event with BCG Toronto and discover what management consulting is all about!

BCG Toronto is at the forefront of key industries, offering specialized expertise in areas such as:

* Digital & Technology: Driving digital transformations that redefine industries.
* Healthcare & Pharmaceuticals: Innovating patient care and drug development.
* Financial Services: Enhancing performance in a rapidly evolving market.
* Industrial Goods: Optimizing operations and strategies in manufacturing and more.
* Consumer Products: Shaping the future of retail and consumer behavior.

This is your opportunity to connect with consultants who are making a difference on a global scale, right here in Toronto.

Don’t miss out — join us and start your journey towards a career in consulting with one of the world’s leading firms by clicking the link in our bio!

Passionate about women’s health research? Apply to join Women’s Health Collective’s mentorship program! 📣💗

We are now accepting applications for mentees and mentors!📄 Mentees must be a first or second year undergraduate student with an interest in learning about careers and research in women’s health. Mentors must be a third or fourth year undergraduate student with experience in women’s health research.

Sign up by filling out the google form linked in our bio! Deadline to apply is by Monday September 30th at 11:59 pm EST.⏰

We are very excited to share our new event with NVIDIA: our Women in Technology Panel! 👩‍💼 NVIDIA is the Engine of AI with CPUs, GPUs, and DPUs at its foundation — join us to explore the path to a career at NVIDIA.

Hear from Nancy Argawal and Jyothi Kolli as they share their unique career journeys, innovative projects and what a typical day in their roles look like.

🗓️ October 2, 2024
📍 Microsoft Teams (link sent after registering)
⏰ 4:00 - 5:00 PM EST

Register with link in bio!

Don’t miss out on an opportunity to gain insider advice!

In honor of the new school year, we’re excited to invite you to our annual First Year Mixer! ✨📣 

This is a great opportunity to connect with fellow first-years and meet upper-years in STEM. You’ll get to hear about their experiences with classes, clubs, research, and more, while sharing your own stories and enjoying some delicious free food! 🥳🍕

Although the event is aimed at first-year female-identifying students in STEM, everyone is welcome to join! 

🗓️ Tuesday, September 17, 2024
⏰ 6:00-8:00 PM
📍 BA2155

⭐ RSVP using the link in bio! 

We hope to see you all there!

WISE Industry Mentorship Program 24-25 is now opening applications for Mentees! 💫

The Industry Mentorship Program will pair current University of Toronto students with industry professionals or individuals pursuing advanced degrees in various fields, such as research, academia, computer science, engineering, healthcare, etc.

This program offers a valuable opportunity to learn from professionals, receive expert guidance, and build lasting connections! 🤝 It’s designed not only for students curious about industry but also for those interested in research or pursuing higher education.

🗓️ Apply through the link in our bio by September 20, 2024, 11:59 PM EST

💭 Contact industry.mentorship@wise.skule.ca for any further questions

Thanks for visiting us at the EngSoc & UTSU Club Fairs! ♡ We had an amazing time chatting with you all! 

In case you didn’t get a chance to meet us, WISE aims to empower, celebrate, and connect women in STEM careers and fields of study. We support cis/trans women, 2-spirit and non-binary folks, and actively work towards dismantling stigmas related to these minority groups in STEM contexts. 

Throughout the year, we host our annual National Conference (@wise.conference), as well as galas, networking events, workshops, and more! Join us at these open-invitation events to celebrate the achievements of our community. 🥂

Interested? 🤔 Join us as a First-Year Rep or General Member, link in bio! APPLICATIONS CLOSE SOON! 📣
